## Why This Is Asked
Examines ability to tame CPU scheduling and memory reclaim in multi-tenant Linux deployments under bursty workloads.

## Key Concepts
- cgroup v2 cpu.max and CPU weight for per-tenant QoS
- cpuset and CPU affinity to confine tenants
- memory reclaim behavior and swappiness tuning
- BPF-based observability for per-tenant latency, IRQs, cache misses
- phased testing, safe rollback, and controlled rollouts

## Code Example
```javascript
// Lightweight latency probe template (pseudo)
